			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">How about a line of series that is a pet only buff that both Beastlords and Magicians get at same level rank that would grant the pet with HP buff and asorb melee migration for their defense that is purposely for PoP zones?
<br />

<br />
Heres my reason:
<br />

<br />
The concerns of PoP:
<br />

<br />
1- The mobs there hit hard, and are abit harsh with stun from hitting/bashing on you and there's almost a guarantee that you will die from it. 
<br />

<br />
2- Pets seem not to last that long at all. Have anyone seen what happen to mages if their pet dies? Beastlords warder doesnt last that long either. It's not even funny.
<br />

<br />
3- No survival along with the pets if we get adds if enchanter died/ld/gated or no enchanter in group. Period.
<br />

<br />

<br />
The support for the pet/warder:
<br />

<br />
1- With this pet buff, survivablity in Planar may improved. Perhaps even more group desired.
<br />

<br />
2- Necromancers, Enchanters and Druids should not have this spell because of Dire Charm and it would consider overpowered. Seems to have plenty of green con mobs for them to DC on in alot of planar zones.  Perhaps add something in the spell that wont allow them to cast it on their DC pets if they were to have this spell?
<br />

<br />
3- See more variety classes grouped, I'm sick of seeing must have warr/cleric/enchanter then any random other classes. If yer from Bertoxx server that is <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
The conclusion: 
<br />

<br />
whats your thought of this? any pros and cons you see on this? why should or shouldnt we have this spell?
<br />

<br />
-Jing</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
