			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I haven't had trouble having my pet tank in any of the first tier planes.  I'm 57 now and since 54 or so my husband's same level mage and I have duo'd in the planes (not solo'd mind you, duo'd) with little difficulty.  Even better when we have a shaman with us, but we can handle just fine as two.
<br />

<br />
We started with flies in PoD until 55.  But since then we pull goos, rats, spiders and easily take one at a time and have occasionally taken two mobs at a time.  
<br />

<br />
Typically speaking, if it's just the two of us, I do not melee.  I play the boring role of pet healer, slower, buffer, nuker.  I will often step in and fight for a bit, until I lose a cpl of bubbles of health, then back off and heal myself up (a little easier now with greater heal and chloro).
<br />

<br />
At 54 we used to have to chain cast pets a lot.  At 56+ that was no longer necessary.  Which is nice now that he can summon pet haste masks.
<br />

<br />
Our pets have no trouble tanking these mobs and with C3 up, there's no trouble keeping up with the mana.  We rarely need to rest between fights.
<br />

<br />
I have never tried to solo up there, so can't speak to that.
<br />

<br />
I have no complaints about either of our pets ability to take the damage. 
<br />

<br />
My only complaint as a pet class is that there is no way for the pets to take aggro off me and I like to melee ;o)  It's funny..pre 40s the two pets could hold aggro, esp with mine procing and his procing water or air pet.  But not since I hit early 40s.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
